The European Union will crumble if it does not return half of its powers to members states, former French president Nicolas Sarkozy has said.

Sarkozy, who is once again campaigning to lead the country, claims ’the system will explode’ if the EU continues to work in its current Brussels-centric form.

The 59-year-old said the EU should only deal with industry, agriculture, competition, trade negotiations, energy and research.

