Speaking from Mulhouse, near the German border, as part of his campaign to become leader of the UMP party once more, Sarkozy said: ’Europe must give back 50 per cent of its competences to member states.’

’If not, the system is going to explode.’

‘I no longer believe in the possibility of changing things in Europe from the inside,’ he told the audience according to The Times.

Sarkozy has promised that, if he is re-elected as president in 2017, that he will withhold all French business with the EU until Brussels meets his demands for reform.

This follows his controversial promise to ‘repeal’ Socialist legislation allowing same-sex unions.

